('The Road Less Traveled by M. Scott Peck', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=105', 'Psychology of love, traditional values, and spiritual growth.', 'Published in 1978, this book by M. Scott Peck combines psychology and spirituality to explore love, traditional values, and spiritual growth. The book emphasizes discipline, love, and grace as paths to personal development.'),
('Man''s Search for Meaning by Viktor Frankl', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=106', 'Holocaust survivor''s account of finding meaning in suffering.', 'Published in 1946, this book by Viktor Frankl recounts his experiences as a Holocaust survivor and his psychological theory of finding meaning in suffering. The book explores the human capacity for resilience and purpose.'),
('The Art of Happiness by Dalai Lama', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=107', 'Buddhist perspective on achieving happiness and inner peace.', 'Published in 1998, this book by the Dalai Lama offers Buddhist wisdom on achieving happiness and inner peace. The book combines Eastern philosophy with Western psychology to provide practical guidance for living a happy life.'),
('The Happiness Project by Gretchen Rubin', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=108', 'Year-long experiment to increase happiness and well-being.', 'Published in 2009, this book by Gretchen Rubin chronicles her year-long experiment to increase happiness and well-being. The book offers practical strategies and insights for creating more joy in everyday life.'),
('The Gifts of Imperfection by Brené Brown', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=109', 'Guide to wholehearted living and embracing imperfection.', 'Published in 2010, this book by Brené Brown explores how to cultivate courage, compassion, and connection in our lives. The book teaches readers to embrace their imperfections and live wholeheartedly.'),
('Daring Greatly by Brené Brown', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=110', 'How the courage to be vulnerable transforms the way we live.', 'Published in 2012, this book by Brené Brown explores how vulnerability and courage can transform our lives. The book argues that embracing vulnerability is essential for meaningful connections and personal growth.'),
('Rising Strong by Brené Brown', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=111', 'How the ability to reset transforms the way we live, love, and lead.', 'Published in 2015, this book by Brené Brown examines how to get back up after falling and transform failure into wisdom. The book offers a process for rising strong from difficult experiences.'),
('Braving the Wilderness by Brené Brown', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=112', 'The quest for true belonging and the courage to stand alone.', 'Published in 2017, this book by Brené Brown explores the quest for true belonging and the courage to stand alone. The book examines how to find connection in an increasingly polarized world.'),
('Atlas Shrugged by Ayn Rand', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=113', 'Novel exploring objectivism and the role of the individual in society.', 'Published in 1957, this novel by Ayn Rand explores her philosophy of objectivism through the story of industrialists who go on strike. The book examines themes of individualism, capitalism, and the role of government.'),
('The Fountainhead by Ayn Rand', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=114', 'Novel about individualism and the creative spirit.', 'Published in 1943, this novel by Ayn Rand tells the story of Howard Roark, an architect who refuses to compromise his artistic vision. The book explores themes of individualism, integrity, and the creative spirit.'),
