('The City of Mirrors by Justin Cronin', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=425', 'Third book in The Passage trilogy.', 'Published in 2016, this conclusion to the trilogy follows the characters as they face the final threat and discover the truth about the world. The book explores themes of final threat, truth, and the resolution of the major conflict.'),
('The Passage by Justin Cronin', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=426', 'First book in The Passage trilogy.', 'Published in 2010, this post-apocalyptic novel follows the survivors of a vampire apocalypse as they try to survive and find answers. The book explores themes of survival, apocalypse, and the search for answers.'),
('The Gunslinger by Stephen King', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=429', 'First book in The Dark Tower series.', 'Published in 1982, this first book introduces Roland Deschain and his quest for the Dark Tower. The book explores themes of introduction, quest, and the beginning of an epic journey.'),
('The Drawing of the Three by Stephen King', 'https://picsum.photos/536/354?random=421', 'Second book in The Dark Tower series.', 'Published in 1987, this sequel follows Roland as he draws three people from different worlds to join his quest. The book explores themes of drawing, joining, and the ongoing development of the quest.'),
